<h2>Jersey Library</h2>
<p>Jersey Library offers a range of materials for borrowing, including books, audio CDs and cassettes, DVDs and music scores. It's free to borrow from the library and everyone can apply to <a href="http://www.gov.je/Leisure/Libraries/Pages/Joining.aspx">join.</a></p>
<p>
There is a free online reservation and renewal service and you can even download magazines.</p>
<p>There are two libraries, the main branch is in St Helier, Halkett Place and there is also a branch at Les Quennevais.</p>
<p>You can find out opening times <a href="http://www.gov.je/Leisure/Libraries/Pages/OpenHours.aspx">here.</a></p>
<p>It is easy to search the <a href="http://capitadiscovery.co.uk/jersey/">library catalogue</a>to see if the book you want is in, and if not, to reserve it.</p>

